author: @ems9097

text:
¬†@ems9097¬†, Sure, there are lots of good pubs in London and I have lots of recommendations. Here are a few of my favourites for food: 
1. The Anchor and Hope (the one in Southwark on The Cut)- I‚Äôve been for dinner a few times and it‚Äôs always excellent, but I‚Äôve never been for Sunday roast 
2. Marksman- Excellent food and I can vouch for their Sunday roast 
3. The Duke of Richmond (the one on Queensbridge Road in East London)- Also all around good food and excellent Sunday roast 
4. The Drappers Arms- Also all around good food and excellent Sunday roast 
5. The Harwood Arms- One Michelin starred pub with possibly the most famous Sunday roast 
6. The Windsor Castle- Very good food and excellent choice if you‚Äôre in Nottingham Hill and the weather is good, as they have a nice back garden; I‚Äôve never had a Sunday roast there though 
7. The Mall Tavern- Also in Notting Hill; excellent burgers; I‚Äôm not sure about their roast specifically though 
8. The Camberwell Arms- Well known for their Sunday roast 
9. The Red Lion and Sun- Excellent option for food and Sunday roast 
10. The French House- Well known pub for the theatre crowd with very good food; it gets really crowded and I can‚Äôt speak to their Sunday roast (even if they do one) though 
Obviously, I don‚Äôt know where you‚Äôll be staying, so I tried to give a selection throughout London, not just in one area. I hope this helps.
